
STEP 1: Install kubectl (Kubernetes CLI)
Ubuntu

sudo apt update
sudo apt install -y kubectl
Verify

kubectl version --client



STEP 2: Install Minikube (Local Kubernetes Cluster)
Install

curl -LO https://storage.googleapis.com/minikube/releases/latest/minikube-linux-amd64
sudo install minikube-linux-amd64 /usr/local/bin/minikube
Verify

minikube version 


STEP 3: Start Kubernetes Cluster

minikube start
Check cluster status:

kubectl cluster-info
Check nodes:

kubectl get nodes


STEP 4: Create Your First Deployment
Create deployment (Nginx example)

kubectl create deployment nginx-app --image=nginx

Check deployment:

kubectl get deployments
Check pods:

kubectl get pods


STEP 5: Expose Application (Service)
Expose deployment as a service:

kubectl expose deployment nginx-app --type=NodePort --port=80
Check services:

kubectl get services
Access app in browser:

minikube service nginx-app

STEP 6: Describe & Debug Resources
Describe pod

kubectl describe pod <pod-name>
View logs

kubectl logs <pod-name>
Login into container

kubectl exec -it <pod-name> -- /bin/bash



STEP 7: Scale Application
Scale pods manually:

kubectl scale deployment nginx-app --replicas=3
Verify:

kubectl get pods



STEP 8: Use YAML (Recommended Way)
Generate deployment YAML

kubectl create deployment nginx-yaml --image=nginx --dry-run=client -o yaml > deployment.yaml
Apply YAML:

kubectl apply -f deployment.yaml


STEP 9: Update Application (Rolling Update)
Update image:

kubectl set image deployment/nginx-app nginx=nginx:latest
Check rollout:

kubectl rollout status deployment nginx-app
Rollback if needed:

kubectl rollout undo deployment nginx-app


STEP 10: Namespaces (Optional but Important)
Create namespace:

kubectl create namespace dev
Deploy in namespace:

kubectl apply -f deployment.yaml -n dev
List resources:

kubectl get all -n dev


STEP 11: Clean Up
Delete deployment:

kubectl delete deployment nginx-app
Delete service:

kubectl delete service nginx-app
Stop cluster:

minikube stop
Delete cluster:

minikube delete

